name: EagleWings Loft

reviews.text: A group of us had our walk at the green corridor and we decided to drop by this pet friendly place. We enjoyed our branch outside as we have dogs. The staff were friendly and they have blower fan to keep us cool. Food price is expected as usual but the root beer float was great. Overall the experience was great.

üçüüçîA wonderful place to dine at! I went here a while ago, and I loved it. We ordered pizza and fries and it was very delicious. We also got our food before 15 minutes had passed. Overall, it was a good restaurant and I'd definetely visit once again! I'd recommend anyone to try this restaurantüçΩüçï!

Lovely little brunch spot. Service and quality has been consistent over the years I've been visiting. The Full Steam Ahead Breakfast has always been the go to, each component is well prepared and  ingredients used are fresh and of high quality, especially the bread, the bread they serve is always fantastic.
Great food in a great atmosphere! Camille's service is great, too. I highly recommend coming here and trying their tom yum bee hoon and seafood pizza!

For me, a place to visit whenever I am craving for Western food. Headed by Lawrence, every staff here is super friendly. Lawrence makes good food recommendations and has always make my meal here a memorable one. Had the Shipwreck Pizza this time and it was delicious. This place also has a few Chinese dishes like Fish Soup, etc... Will be back for more.
